<tool id="tool_remove_water" name="Remove Water" version="2.0.0">

    <description>
        reading a file gromacs of water + file generated by grompp of type tpr + topology file to output in gro format.
        <!-- lê um arquivo gromacs de água + arquivo gerado pelo grompp do tipo tpr + arquivo de topologia para gerar a saída em formato gro. -->
    </description>

    <command interpreter="python">

        remover_agua.py $input_gro $input_tpr $input_top $source_distance $output_gro $output_top

    </command>

    <inputs>
        <param format="gro" name="input_gro" type="data" label="Source file GRO"/>
        <param format="tpr" name="input_tpr" type="data" label="Source file TPR"/>
        <param format="top" name="input_top" type="data" label="Source file TOP"/>

        <param name="source_distance" type="float" max="1.0" min="0" value="0.5" label="Distance"/>
    </inputs>

    <outputs>
        <data format="gro" name="output_gro" label="Gromacs File by Remove Water"/>
        <data format="top" name="output_top" label="Topology File by Remove Water"/>
    </outputs>

    <help>
        This tool has the purpose of removing the waters 5A protein and consequently updating the amount of water topology, in which the output is a file without the "layer" of water around the protein and in the cavities, with the updated topology.
        <!--Esta tool tem a finalidade de remover as águas a 5A da proteína e consequentemente atualizar a quantidade de águas da topologia, na qual a saída será um arquivo sem a "camada" de águas ao redor da proteína e dentro das cavidades, junto a topologia atualizada.-->
    </help>

</tool>
